### Code Documentation

- Document public APIs and exported functions
- Explain complex algorithms or business logic
- Document type constraints and assumptions
- Include usage examples for utility functions

### When to Comment

- Complex algorithms or logic that isn't immediately obvious
- Business rules or domain-specific logic
- Workarounds or temporary solutions
- Performance optimizations that might seem counterintuitive
- Edge cases or special handling

### When NOT to Comment

- Self-explanatory code (good code is self-documenting)
- Obvious variable names or simple operations
- Comments that just repeat what the code does

### Documentation Style

- Use clear, concise Korean language
- Use proper grammar and punctuation
- Include code examples when helpful
- Use markdown formatting in JSDoc when appropriate

